(this name uses eastern slavic naming customs; the patronymic is andreevna and the family name is pogonina.) natalia andreevna pogonina (russian: наталья андреевна погонина; born 9 march 1985) is a russian chess player who holds the fide title of woman grandmaster (wgm). she is the runner-up of the women's world chess championship 2015. pogonina was a member of the gold medal-winning russian team at the women's chess olympiads of 2012 and 2014, and at the 2011 women's european team chess championship.